Menthol Marketing to the LGBTQ Community
LGBTQ youth and adults smoke at higher rates than the general
population due to industry targeting, social norms centered around
bar culture, and minority stress, including lack of family acceptance.
Menthol use in the LGBTQ community
For decades, the tobacco industry has targeted African Americans,
women, youth, and the LGBTQ community with menthol marketing
through advertisements and music events. More recently, tobacco
companies have targeted menthol marketing to traditionally safe
spaces for the LGBTQ community, like bars and Pride festivals, through
event sponsorship and coupons to buy packs for $1.
